Try [this excellent solution from darrelgrainger.blogspot.com](http://darrellgrainger.blogspot.com/2012/06/staleelementexception.html):

    public boolean retryingFindClick(By by) {
        boolean result = false;
        int attempts = 0;
        while(attempts &lt; 2) {
            try {
                driver.findElement(by).click();
                result = true;
                break;
            } catch(StaleElementException e) {
            }
            attempts++;
        }
        return result;
    }

Generally this is due to the DOM being updated and you trying to access an updated/new element -- but the DOM&#39;s refreshed so it&#39;s an invalid reference you have..

