The Apache Commons Text library maps the values directly to the names.  
[Apache Commons Text - EntityArrays.java](https://github.com/apache/commons-text/blob/master/src/main/java/org/apache/commons/text/translate/EntityArrays.java#L376)

You can create your own implementation, using the basic set, `&quot;`, `&amp;`, `&lt;`, and `&gt;`.

```java
String escape(String string) {
    StringBuilder escaped = new StringBuilder();
    for (char character : string.toCharArray()) {
        switch (character) {
            case &#39;&quot;&#39;, &#39;&amp;&#39;, &#39;&lt;&#39;, &#39;&gt;&#39; -&gt; {
                escaped.append(&quot;&amp;#%d;&quot;.formatted((int) character));
            }
            default -&gt; escaped.append(character);
        }
    }
    return escaped.toString();
}
```

Input

```none
