You can try using Junit5&#39;s `@Nested` annotation. This will allow a common setup of a group of tests and it will also show the test report very nicely in your IDE. You would be able to use it like so:

```java
class Test {
    // RepetitionInfo info1 = ... // will be available for all

    @Nested
    @RepeatedTest(...)
    class ChildTest {
        RepetitionInfo info2 = ... // will be available for this class only

        @RepeatedTest(...)
        public void test() {
           ... // you can use info1 + info2 here
        }
        @RepeatedTest(...)
        public void test2() {
           ... // you can use info1 + info2 here
        }
    }

    @Nested
    @RepeatedTest(...)
    class ChildTest3 {
        RepetitionInfo info3 = ... // will be available for this class only
        // ... // you can use info1 + info3
    }
}

```
